provisions.content:
_ In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,―
(a)    “Chairman” means the Chairman of the Council;
(b)    “Council” means the National Security Council established under section 3;
(c)    “Government” means the Federal Government or a Provincial Government, as
the case may be;
(d)    “President” means the President of the Islamic Republic of, Pakistan; and
(e)    “Rules” means the rules made under this Act.

for carrying out the purposes of this Act:
Provided that till such time that the rules are made the Council ma with the approval of the
Chairman, follow such procedure as it may fit.
